The paper deals with the effect of interference on the convergence rate of average consensus algorithms in a network of nodes. This involves analyzing the communication and connectivity aspects of the network, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also considers the impact of interference on the system dynamics and control, which are relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a mathematical model and analyzes the convergence properties of the consensus algorithm, which falls under the Mathematical Aspects of Computer Science (cs.MA) sub-category.
